    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-22T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-22T08:00:00-05:00" n="112"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d112">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/3839</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-22T14:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 24, 7.32 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4042. Department’s 2304, July 17. I am assured, informally, that Swiss Government
                    will accept offer to preside over conference and furnish rooms provided German
                    Government agrees. Does Department deem it advisable to inform German Government
                    that Swiss have been asked to preside?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
